title: For Sale:  Utah Concealed Carry Course
postcontent:
TRAC LLC
Training Responsibly Armed Citizens

Interested in getting your Utah Concealed Carry permit?
Now is your chance!!!

I live in Wisconsin, why would I want a Utah permit?
If you wish to carry a concealed weapon in another state while on vacation for example, you must either possess that state’s concealed carry permit, or one that the state you are visiting recognizes (or one that has a reciprocity agreement).  Utah is widely recognized as having a large number of states that either offer reciprocal rights, or recognize the Utah permit.

In how many states can I carry with the Utah permit?
As of May 10, 2015 17 states have written reciprocal agreements with Utah and another 18 recognize the Utah permit for a whopping 35 states!

Can I just get a Utah permit and use it in Wisconsin?
No.  Utah insists that if a state that recognizes the Utah permit (Wisconsin is one of these), an applicant must first obtain a Concealed Weapons/Firearms Permit/License from their own state and include a copy of it with their Utah application.  The good news, if you need to obtain your Wisconsin CCW License, I have a course just for you!  Call or email me for further details REDACTED or REDACTED). Please note that Utah Bureau of Criminal Identification specifically notes that you must take their course content and it cannot be taught in conjunction with other states classes.

I’d love to get the Utah permit, what do I do now?
Let me know by email (REDACTED) and I will arrange a registration packet for you.  In that package you will receive a copy of the Utah Concealed Firearm Permit application.
You will also need to get:
•	one set of fingerprints on the fingerprint card that I give you (more on that in the registration packet)
•	a copy of your Wisconsin (or your home state) CCW or CFP with the expiration date clearly visible,
•	a recent color passport photo (2”x2”, no hats or sunglasses) with your name on the back.
After the successful completion of the course you should get a certification letter that will accompany your application and you will get your application stamped with my Certified Instructor’s stamp – this is mandatory for your application.

Truly it is not that difficult, and think of the freedom to carry in so many areas!
The next class will be held the afternoon of Saturday June 13, 2015 at the Holiday Inn Express located in Fort Atkinson at the junction of Highway 12 and Highway 26 REDACTED), details for the time will be mailed out shortly.

Cost for the Utah Class is $85.00
There is a loyalty discount for anyone that has taken the Wisconsin CCW class within the past 12 months.  Call me for details! REDACTED)
